<subSubSection id="E29E656D6E759C75FF06F304FE2416A9" pageId="9" pageNumber="367" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="AA3B36E66E759C75FF06F304FE2416A9" blockId="9.[151,1437,726,2013]" pageId="9" pageNumber="367">
<emphasis id="98F0EAF46E759C75FF06F304FED61675" bold="true" box="[199,334,834,860]" pageId="9" pageNumber="367">Etymology.</emphasis>
This specific name is derived from the 
<typeStatus id="753F88446E759C75FCDEF305FCD71674" box="[799,847,835,861]" pageId="9" pageNumber="367">type</typeStatus>
locality, 
<collectingRegion id="6840F8046E759C75FC7DF304FB951675" box="[956,1037,834,860]" country="China" name="Hainan" pageId="9" pageNumber="367">Hainan</collectingRegion>
Island which is the second largest island in 
<collectingCountry id="D29376766E759C75FF3FF320FEDC16A9" box="[254,324,870,896]" name="China" pageId="9" pageNumber="367">China</collectingCountry>
, adjective.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="E29E656D6E759C75FF06F3CCFA0F111C" pageId="9" pageNumber="367" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="AA3B36E66E759C75FF06F3CCFA0F111C" blockId="9.[151,1437,726,2013]" pageId="9" pageNumber="367">
<emphasis id="98F0EAF46E759C75FF06F3CCFEDA168D" bold="true" box="[199,322,906,932]" pageId="9" pageNumber="367">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
This species with contiguous processes on the coxosternum of the male first leg-pair belongs to the 
<taxonomicName id="6D844D656E759C75FF56F3E8FE1C16E1" authorityName="Carl" authorityYear="1911" box="[151,388,942,968]" class="Diplopoda" family="Cambalopsidae" genus="Glyphiulus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Spirostreptida" pageId="9" pageNumber="367" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="javanicus">
<emphasis id="98F0EAF46E759C75FF56F3E8FE1C16E1" box="[151,388,942,968]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="367">Glyphiulus javanicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
-group, and it can be separated from other species in this group by (1) the crests on the collum being complete and developed, and the carinotaxic formula I–III + P + M (
<figureCitation id="32BF2A636E759C75FC0BF394FBBA16C4" box="[970,1058,978,1005]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="10.[151,250,1688,1712]" captionTargetBox="[153,1434,181,1665]" captionTargetId="figure-20@10.[153,1434,181,1665]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 6. Male of Glyphiulus hainanensis sp. nov., paratype. A. anterior part of body, anterior view; B. body ring, posterior view; C. midbody rings, dorsal view; D. midbody rings, lateral view; E. posterior part of body, ventral view; F. posterior part of body, lateral view. Abbreviations: ant, antennae; co, collum; dt, dorsal tooth; e, eyes; ep, epiproct; h, head; hy, hypoproct; me, metazonite; ot, ozoporiferous tubercle; pa, paraproct; pr, prozonite; wl, walking leg. Scale bars: 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6592969" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6592969/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="367">Fig. 6A</figureCitation>
); (2) male legs I 2 or 3 segmented, slightly longer than the coxosternal process (
<figureCitation id="32BF2A636E759C75FD5DF3B0FD611139" box="[668,761,1014,1040]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="11.[151,250,716,740]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,181,692]" captionTargetId="figure-29@11.[151,1435,181,692]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURE 7. Male of Glyphiulus hainanensis sp. nov., paratype. A. male legs 1, anterior view; B. male leg 6; C. midbody leg. Abbreviations: cs, coxosternum; csp, coxosternal process; ft, femoral tubercle; t, telopodite. Scale bars: 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6592971" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6592971/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="367">Fig. 7A</figureCitation>
); (3) the coxite process of the anterior gonopod prolonged strightly, with a sharp tip (
<figureCitation id="32BF2A636E759C75FE7CF45CFD8F111D" box="[445,535,1050,1076]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="11.[151,250,1636,1660]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,801,1613]" captionTargetId="figure-74@11.[151,1435,801,1613]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURE 8. Gonopods of Glyphiulus hainanensis sp. nov., paratype. A. anterior gonopods, posterior view; B. posterior gonopods, anterior view. Abbreviations: c, coxite; cp, coxite process; f, flagellum; l, lamelliform lobe; t, telopodite. Scale bars: A. 0.4 mm; B. 0.3 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6592973" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6592973/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="367">Fig. 8A</figureCitation>
); (4) male femora VI and VII modified, with a tubercle distoventrally (
<figureCitation id="32BF2A636E759C75FAF3F45CFA13111C" box="[1330,1419,1050,1077]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="11.[151,250,716,740]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,181,692]" captionTargetId="figure-29@11.[151,1435,181,692]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURE 7. Male of Glyphiulus hainanensis sp. nov., paratype. A. male legs 1, anterior view; B. male leg 6; C. midbody leg. Abbreviations: cs, coxosternum; csp, coxosternal process; ft, femoral tubercle; t, telopodite. Scale bars: 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6592971" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6592971/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="367">Fig. 7B</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="E29E656D6E759C75FF06F478FE2112BD" pageId="9" pageNumber="367" type="description">
<paragraph id="AA3B36E66E759C75FF06F478FE661189" blockId="9.[151,1437,726,2013]" pageId="9" pageNumber="367">
<emphasis id="98F0EAF46E759C75FF06F478FEC11171" bold="true" box="[199,345,1086,1112]" pageId="9" pageNumber="367">Description.</emphasis>
Body segments with 59–70p + 1–4a + T (
<typeStatus id="753F88446E759C75FCE9F478FC141171" box="[808,908,1086,1112]" pageId="9" pageNumber="367">holotype</typeStatus>
68p + 1a + T). Body size of ca. 
<quantity id="6D7C9B036E759C75FB2CF478FAFD1170" box="[1261,1381,1086,1113]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.05" metricValueMax="5.7" metricValueMin="4.4" pageId="9" pageNumber="367" unit="mm" value="50.5" valueMax="57.0" valueMin="44.0">44–57 mm</quantity>
long and 2.3–3.0 mm wide (
<typeStatus id="753F88446E759C75FE5FF424FD9A1155" box="[414,514,1122,1148]" pageId="9" pageNumber="367">holotype</typeStatus>
54 and 
<quantity id="6D7C9B036E759C75FDA1F424FD211154" box="[608,697,1122,1149]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.6" pageId="9" pageNumber="367" unit="mm" value="2.6">2.6 mm</quantity>
, respectively). Color generally earthy yellow, with ozoporiferous tubercles light yellow (
<figureCitation id="32BF2A636E759C75FE58F4C0FE691189" box="[409,497,1158,1184]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1886,1910]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,957,1861]" captionTargetId="figure-304@2.[151,1435,957,1863]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Habitus and habitats of Glyphiulus fortis sp. nov. and Glyphiulus hainanensis sp. nov. A. habitus of G. fortis sp. nov.; B. the entrance to Baimo Cave where G. fortis sp. nov. inhabited; C. habitus of G. hainanensis sp. nov.; D. habitat of G. hainanensis sp. nov." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6592957" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6592957/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="367">Fig. 1C</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="AA3B36E66E759C75FF06F4ECFEB31019" blockId="9.[151,1437,726,2013]" pageId="9" pageNumber="367">
<emphasis id="98F0EAF46E759C75FF06F4ECFE9611ED" bold="true" box="[199,270,1194,1220]" pageId="9" pageNumber="367">Head.</emphasis>
Each eye patch with 20–22 pigmented eyes arranged in two or three regular linear rows (
<figureCitation id="32BF2A636E759C75FAF3F4ECFA1711EC" box="[1330,1423,1194,1221]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="10.[151,250,1688,1712]" captionTargetBox="[153,1434,181,1665]" captionTargetId="figure-20@10.[153,1434,181,1665]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 6. Male of Glyphiulus hainanensis sp. nov., paratype. A. anterior part of body, anterior view; B. body ring, posterior view; C. midbody rings, dorsal view; D. midbody rings, lateral view; E. posterior part of body, ventral view; F. posterior part of body, lateral view. Abbreviations: ant, antennae; co, collum; dt, dorsal tooth; e, eyes; ep, epiproct; h, head; hy, hypoproct; me, metazonite; ot, ozoporiferous tubercle; pa, paraproct; pr, prozonite; wl, walking leg. Scale bars: 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6592969" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6592969/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="367">Fig. 6A</figureCitation>
). Antennae (
<figureCitation id="32BF2A636E759C75FED5F488FEF611C0" box="[276,366,1230,1257]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="10.[151,250,1688,1712]" captionTargetBox="[153,1434,181,1665]" captionTargetId="figure-20@10.[153,1434,181,1665]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 6. Male of Glyphiulus hainanensis sp. nov., paratype. A. anterior part of body, anterior view; B. body ring, posterior view; C. midbody rings, dorsal view; D. midbody rings, lateral view; E. posterior part of body, ventral view; F. posterior part of body, lateral view. Abbreviations: ant, antennae; co, collum; dt, dorsal tooth; e, eyes; ep, epiproct; h, head; hy, hypoproct; me, metazonite; ot, ozoporiferous tubercle; pa, paraproct; pr, prozonite; wl, walking leg. Scale bars: 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6592969" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6592969/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="367">Fig. 6A</figureCitation>
) slender, densely setose. Antennomeres 1, 6–7 cylindrical, 2–5 clavate. Relative antennomere lengths 5≥3&gt;4≥2≥6&gt;1≥7. Labrum with four teeth anteromedially. Gnathochilarium with a separate promentum, polytrichous.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="AA3B36E66E759C75FF06F57CFB18107C" blockId="9.[151,1437,726,2013]" box="[199,1152,1338,1365]" pageId="9" pageNumber="367">
<emphasis id="98F0EAF46E759C75FF06F57CFEBF107D" bold="true" box="[199,295,1338,1364]" pageId="9" pageNumber="367">Collum.</emphasis>
All crests complete and strong, carinotaxic formula I–III + P + M (
<figureCitation id="32BF2A636E759C75FBD8F57CFBEB107C" box="[1049,1139,1338,1365]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="10.[151,250,1688,1712]" captionTargetBox="[153,1434,181,1665]" captionTargetId="figure-20@10.[153,1434,181,1665]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 6. Male of Glyphiulus hainanensis sp. nov., paratype. A. anterior part of body, anterior view; B. body ring, posterior view; C. midbody rings, dorsal view; D. midbody rings, lateral view; E. posterior part of body, ventral view; F. posterior part of body, lateral view. Abbreviations: ant, antennae; co, collum; dt, dorsal tooth; e, eyes; ep, epiproct; h, head; hy, hypoproct; me, metazonite; ot, ozoporiferous tubercle; pa, paraproct; pr, prozonite; wl, walking leg. Scale bars: 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6592969" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6592969/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="367">Fig. 6A</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="AA3B36E66E759C75FF06F518FE0610CC" blockId="9.[151,1437,726,2013]" pageId="9" pageNumber="367">
<emphasis id="98F0EAF46E759C75FF06F518FECB1051" bold="true" box="[199,339,1374,1400]" pageId="9" pageNumber="367">Body rings.</emphasis>
Postcollum constriction modest. Tegument rough (
<figureCitation id="32BF2A636E759C75FC65F518FBDE1050" box="[932,1094,1374,1401]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="10.[151,250,1688,1712]" captionTargetBox="[153,1434,181,1665]" captionTargetId="figure-20@10.[153,1434,181,1665]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 6. Male of Glyphiulus hainanensis sp. nov., paratype. A. anterior part of body, anterior view; B. body ring, posterior view; C. midbody rings, dorsal view; D. midbody rings, lateral view; E. posterior part of body, ventral view; F. posterior part of body, lateral view. Abbreviations: ant, antennae; co, collum; dt, dorsal tooth; e, eyes; ep, epiproct; h, head; hy, hypoproct; me, metazonite; ot, ozoporiferous tubercle; pa, paraproct; pr, prozonite; wl, walking leg. Scale bars: 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6592969" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6592969/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="367">Fig. 6C, D, F</figureCitation>
). Metatergal strongly crested, carinotaxic formula 2/2+I/i+3/3+I/i+2/2 (
<figureCitation id="32BF2A636E759C75FDA8F5C4FD7E10B4" box="[617,742,1410,1437]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="10.[151,250,1688,1712]" captionTargetBox="[153,1434,181,1665]" captionTargetId="figure-20@10.[153,1434,181,1665]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 6. Male of Glyphiulus hainanensis sp. nov., paratype. A. anterior part of body, anterior view; B. body ring, posterior view; C. midbody rings, dorsal view; D. midbody rings, lateral view; E. posterior part of body, ventral view; F. posterior part of body, lateral view. Abbreviations: ant, antennae; co, collum; dt, dorsal tooth; e, eyes; ep, epiproct; h, head; hy, hypoproct; me, metazonite; ot, ozoporiferous tubercle; pa, paraproct; pr, prozonite; wl, walking leg. Scale bars: 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6592969" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6592969/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="367">Fig. 6B–D</figureCitation>
). Ozoporiferous tubercles with rounded tip, as high as broad, larger than other tubercles (
<figureCitation id="32BF2A636E759C75FE17F5E0FDCD10E8" box="[470,597,1446,1473]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="10.[151,250,1688,1712]" captionTargetBox="[153,1434,181,1665]" captionTargetId="figure-20@10.[153,1434,181,1665]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 6. Male of Glyphiulus hainanensis sp. nov., paratype. A. anterior part of body, anterior view; B. body ring, posterior view; C. midbody rings, dorsal view; D. midbody rings, lateral view; E. posterior part of body, ventral view; F. posterior part of body, lateral view. Abbreviations: ant, antennae; co, collum; dt, dorsal tooth; e, eyes; ep, epiproct; h, head; hy, hypoproct; me, metazonite; ot, ozoporiferous tubercle; pa, paraproct; pr, prozonite; wl, walking leg. Scale bars: 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6592969" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6592969/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="367">Fig. 6B–D</figureCitation>
). Lateral crests fully developed (
<figureCitation id="32BF2A636E759C75FC10F5E0FBEA10E8" box="[977,1138,1446,1473]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="10.[151,250,1688,1712]" captionTargetBox="[153,1434,181,1665]" captionTargetId="figure-20@10.[153,1434,181,1665]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 6. Male of Glyphiulus hainanensis sp. nov., paratype. A. anterior part of body, anterior view; B. body ring, posterior view; C. midbody rings, dorsal view; D. midbody rings, lateral view; E. posterior part of body, ventral view; F. posterior part of body, lateral view. Abbreviations: ant, antennae; co, collum; dt, dorsal tooth; e, eyes; ep, epiproct; h, head; hy, hypoproct; me, metazonite; ot, ozoporiferous tubercle; pa, paraproct; pr, prozonite; wl, walking leg. Scale bars: 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6592969" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6592969/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="367">Fig. 6B, D, F</figureCitation>
). Midbody rings round in cross-section (
<figureCitation id="32BF2A636E759C75FEF8F58CFE0910CC" box="[313,401,1482,1509]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="10.[151,250,1688,1712]" captionTargetBox="[153,1434,181,1665]" captionTargetId="figure-20@10.[153,1434,181,1665]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 6. Male of Glyphiulus hainanensis sp. nov., paratype. A. anterior part of body, anterior view; B. body ring, posterior view; C. midbody rings, dorsal view; D. midbody rings, lateral view; E. posterior part of body, ventral view; F. posterior part of body, lateral view. Abbreviations: ant, antennae; co, collum; dt, dorsal tooth; e, eyes; ep, epiproct; h, head; hy, hypoproct; me, metazonite; ot, ozoporiferous tubercle; pa, paraproct; pr, prozonite; wl, walking leg. Scale bars: 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6592969" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6592969/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="367">Fig. 6B</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="AA3B36E66E759C75FF06F5A8FCF81304" blockId="9.[151,1437,726,2013]" pageId="9" pageNumber="367">
<emphasis id="98F0EAF46E759C75FF06F5A8FE831321" bold="true" box="[199,283,1518,1544]" pageId="9" pageNumber="367">Telson.</emphasis>
Epiproct simple, with a rounded caudal ridge and a small dorsal tooth (
<figureCitation id="32BF2A636E759C75FB99F5A8FB371320" box="[1112,1199,1518,1545]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="10.[151,250,1688,1712]" captionTargetBox="[153,1434,181,1665]" captionTargetId="figure-20@10.[153,1434,181,1665]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 6. Male of Glyphiulus hainanensis sp. nov., paratype. A. anterior part of body, anterior view; B. body ring, posterior view; C. midbody rings, dorsal view; D. midbody rings, lateral view; E. posterior part of body, ventral view; F. posterior part of body, lateral view. Abbreviations: ant, antennae; co, collum; dt, dorsal tooth; e, eyes; ep, epiproct; h, head; hy, hypoproct; me, metazonite; ot, ozoporiferous tubercle; pa, paraproct; pr, prozonite; wl, walking leg. Scale bars: 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6592969" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6592969/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="367">Fig. 6F</figureCitation>
). Paraprocts convex, polytrichous (
<figureCitation id="32BF2A636E759C75FEF2F654FE3F1304" box="[307,423,1554,1581]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="10.[151,250,1688,1712]" captionTargetBox="[153,1434,181,1665]" captionTargetId="figure-20@10.[153,1434,181,1665]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 6. Male of Glyphiulus hainanensis sp. nov., paratype. A. anterior part of body, anterior view; B. body ring, posterior view; C. midbody rings, dorsal view; D. midbody rings, lateral view; E. posterior part of body, ventral view; F. posterior part of body, lateral view. Abbreviations: ant, antennae; co, collum; dt, dorsal tooth; e, eyes; ep, epiproct; h, head; hy, hypoproct; me, metazonite; ot, ozoporiferous tubercle; pa, paraproct; pr, prozonite; wl, walking leg. Scale bars: 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6592969" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6592969/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="367">Fig. 6E, F</figureCitation>
). Hypoproct crescent-shaped (
<figureCitation id="32BF2A636E759C75FD3DF654FCCB1304" box="[764,851,1554,1581]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="10.[151,250,1688,1712]" captionTargetBox="[153,1434,181,1665]" captionTargetId="figure-20@10.[153,1434,181,1665]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 6. Male of Glyphiulus hainanensis sp. nov., paratype. A. anterior part of body, anterior view; B. body ring, posterior view; C. midbody rings, dorsal view; D. midbody rings, lateral view; E. posterior part of body, ventral view; F. posterior part of body, lateral view. Abbreviations: ant, antennae; co, collum; dt, dorsal tooth; e, eyes; ep, epiproct; h, head; hy, hypoproct; me, metazonite; ot, ozoporiferous tubercle; pa, paraproct; pr, prozonite; wl, walking leg. Scale bars: 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6592969" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6592969/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="367">Fig. 6E</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="AA3B36E66E759C75FF06F670FF50135D" blockId="9.[151,1437,726,2013]" pageId="9" pageNumber="367">
<emphasis id="98F0EAF46E759C75FF06F670FEF31379" bold="true" box="[199,363,1590,1616]" pageId="9" pageNumber="367">Walking legs.</emphasis>
Slender, nearly as long as body width, densely setose, with a fine accessory claw (
<figureCitation id="32BF2A636E759C75FAF8F670FA0F1379" box="[1337,1431,1590,1616]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="10.[151,250,1688,1712]" captionTargetBox="[153,1434,181,1665]" captionTargetId="figure-20@10.[153,1434,181,1665]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 6. Male of Glyphiulus hainanensis sp. nov., paratype. A. anterior part of body, anterior view; B. body ring, posterior view; C. midbody rings, dorsal view; D. midbody rings, lateral view; E. posterior part of body, ventral view; F. posterior part of body, lateral view. Abbreviations: ant, antennae; co, collum; dt, dorsal tooth; e, eyes; ep, epiproct; h, head; hy, hypoproct; me, metazonite; ot, ozoporiferous tubercle; pa, paraproct; pr, prozonite; wl, walking leg. Scale bars: 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6592969" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6592969/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="367">Figs 6B</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="32BF2A636E759C75FF56F61CFF23135D" box="[151,187,1626,1652]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="11.[151,250,716,740]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,181,692]" captionTargetId="figure-29@11.[151,1435,181,692]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURE 7. Male of Glyphiulus hainanensis sp. nov., paratype. A. male legs 1, anterior view; B. male leg 6; C. midbody leg. Abbreviations: cs, coxosternum; csp, coxosternal process; ft, femoral tubercle; t, telopodite. Scale bars: 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6592971" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6592971/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="367">7C</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="AA3B36E66E759C75FF06F638FE2112BD" blockId="9.[151,1437,726,2013]" pageId="9" pageNumber="367">
<emphasis id="98F0EAF46E759C75FF06F638FE7E13B1" bold="true" box="[199,486,1662,1688]" pageId="9" pageNumber="367">Male sexual characters.</emphasis>
Male legs I strongly reduced, 2 or 3 segmented, with a pair of medial coxosternal hooked processes in contact medially (
<figureCitation id="32BF2A636E759C75FD87F6E4FD381395" box="[582,672,1698,1724]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="11.[151,250,716,740]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,181,692]" captionTargetId="figure-29@11.[151,1435,181,692]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURE 7. Male of Glyphiulus hainanensis sp. nov., paratype. A. male legs 1, anterior view; B. male leg 6; C. midbody leg. Abbreviations: cs, coxosternum; csp, coxosternal process; ft, femoral tubercle; t, telopodite. Scale bars: 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6592971" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6592971/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="367">Fig. 7A</figureCitation>
). Femora VI and VII inflated, possess a small tubercle distoventrally (
<figureCitation id="32BF2A636E759C75FF61F680FF6113C8" box="[160,249,1734,1761]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="11.[151,250,716,740]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,181,692]" captionTargetId="figure-29@11.[151,1435,181,692]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURE 7. Male of Glyphiulus hainanensis sp. nov., paratype. A. male legs 1, anterior view; B. male leg 6; C. midbody leg. Abbreviations: cs, coxosternum; csp, coxosternal process; ft, femoral tubercle; t, telopodite. Scale bars: 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6592971" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6592971/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="367">Fig. 7B</figureCitation>
). Coxite of anterior gonopods (
<figureCitation id="32BF2A636E759C75FD9BF680FD2A13C9" box="[602,690,1734,1760]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="11.[151,250,1636,1660]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,801,1613]" captionTargetId="figure-74@11.[151,1435,801,1613]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURE 8. Gonopods of Glyphiulus hainanensis sp. nov., paratype. A. anterior gonopods, posterior view; B. posterior gonopods, anterior view. Abbreviations: c, coxite; cp, coxite process; f, flagellum; l, lamelliform lobe; t, telopodite. Scale bars: A. 0.4 mm; B. 0.3 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6592973" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6592973/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="367">Fig. 8A</figureCitation>
) shield-like, ridged medially, with 1 or 2 lines of microsetae anteriorly. Coxite processes prolonged straightly, with sharp tip, obviously longer than telopodites. Telopodites located laterally, one-segmented, slender, digitiform, with several distal setae and a field of microsetae at base. Coxite of posterior gonopods (
<figureCitation id="32BF2A636E759C75FE41F774FE4E1265" box="[384,470,1842,1868]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="11.[151,250,1636,1660]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,801,1613]" captionTargetId="figure-74@11.[151,1435,801,1613]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURE 8. Gonopods of Glyphiulus hainanensis sp. nov., paratype. A. anterior gonopods, posterior view; B. posterior gonopods, anterior view. Abbreviations: c, coxite; cp, coxite process; f, flagellum; l, lamelliform lobe; t, telopodite. Scale bars: A. 0.4 mm; B. 0.3 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6592973" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6592973/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="367">Fig. 8B</figureCitation>
) with a medial lamelliform lobe and two rows of strong, curved setae at mediolateral margin. Flagella short, slender, and zigzag-edged, situated at the tip of coxite lobe. Lateral margin of coxite with a round field of microsetae.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="E29E656D6E759C75FF06F7D8FA9E1291" box="[199,1286,1950,1977]" pageId="9" pageNumber="367" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph id="AA3B36E66E759C75FF06F7D8FA9E1291" blockId="9.[151,1437,726,2013]" box="[199,1286,1950,1977]" pageId="9" pageNumber="367">
<emphasis id="98F0EAF46E759C75FF06F7D8FEB41291" bold="true" box="[199,300,1950,1976]" pageId="9" pageNumber="367">Ecology.</emphasis>
This species is epigean and was found in the litter layer of a deciduous forest (
<figureCitation id="32BF2A636E759C75FB5EF7D8FB601291" box="[1183,1272,1950,1976]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1886,1910]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,957,1861]" captionTargetId="figure-304@2.[151,1435,957,1863]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Habitus and habitats of Glyphiulus fortis sp. nov. and Glyphiulus hainanensis sp. nov. A. habitus of G. fortis sp. nov.; B. the entrance to Baimo Cave where G. fortis sp. nov. inhabited; C. habitus of G. hainanensis sp. nov.; D. habitat of G. hainanensis sp. nov." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6592957" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6592957/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="367">Fig. 1D</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
